about.summary: Add smoothing spline modelling capability to nlme. Fit smoothing spline terms in Gaussian linear and nonlinear mixed-effects models

name: r-lmesplines
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.1-10' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-lmesplines
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/lmeSplines_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/lmeSplines/lmeSplines_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2a7ae80f3742da6254dcd313a7ffd11bea4832d27b7f06f69f18e733af86c63b

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-nlme >=3.1_29
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-nlme >=3.1_29

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('lmeSplines')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('lmeSplines')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=lmeSplines
  license: GPL-2.0-only
  summary: Add smoothing spline modelling capability to nlme. Fit smoothing spline terms in Gaussian
    linear and nonlinear mixed-effects models
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
